    <h1>Research Page – EcoMart</h1>

    <!-- Research Image -->
    <img src="images/research.jpg" alt="Website research and comparison illustration" class="research-image">

    <!-- Website References Section -->
    <h2>1. Website References</h2>
    <p>The following websites were researched and analyzed for comparison with the EcoMart website:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>earthhero.com – Sustainable e-commerce website</li>
        <li>greenpeace.org – Environmental awareness platform</li>
        <li>patagonia.com – Sustainable clothing brand</li>
        <li>etsy.com – Online marketplace</li>
        <li>amazon.com – Large-scale e-commerce platform</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Similarities Section -->
    <h2>2. Similarities</h2>
    <div class="highlight">
        <ul>
            <li>All websites use a navigation bar for easy access.</li>
            <li>Product-based websites display images, names, and prices.</li>
            <li>Text and images are used to present information clearly.</li>
            <li>Blog or article sections help educate users.</li>
            <li>User-friendly design is a common goal.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Differences Section -->
    <h2>3. Differences</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>EcoMart is a static website, while most researched websites are dynamic.</li>
        <li>Advanced features such as reviews and filters are not included.</li>
        <li>EcoMart uses a simple and clean layout.</li>
        <li>Large websites use backend technologies, EcoMart does not.</li>
        <li>EcoMart focuses equally on education and products.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Improvements Section -->
    <h2>4. Improvements Made in EcoMart</h2>
    <div class="highlight">
        <ul>
            <li>Consistent green-themed color scheme.</li>
            <li>Clear display of discounted and actual prices.</li>
            <li>Easy navigation suitable for all users.</li>
            <li>Functional contact form with JavaScript validation.</li>
            <li>Simple structure for better accessibility.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Conclusion -->
    <h2>5. Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
        This research helped in understanding different website designs and technologies.
        EcoMart improves upon researched websites by maintaining simplicity, accessibility,
        and clarity while still delivering essential e-commerce features.
    </p>

